Class RefrigeratedTruck

  • java.lang.Object
    • delivery.Truck
      • delivery.RefrigeratedTruck

  • public class RefrigeratedTruck
extends Truck
    Class to create a RefrigeratedTruck object that contains Stock at a specified temperature at a cost. This class extends the abstract class Truck.
    Author:
    Tim

    • Constructor Detail

      • RefrigeratedTruck

        public RefrigeratedTruck(Stock contents)
                  throws DeliveryException,
                         StockException
        Constructor for RefrigeratedTruck. Stores contents at a set temperature, and calculates cost to use Truck.
        Parameters:
        contents - Stock object to represent the contents of the Truck.
        Throws:
        DeliveryException - Throws an exception when contents is null, temperature is out of bounds, or use of a RefrigeratedTruck is not needed.
        StockException - Re-throws exceptions thrown by methods used within.
